Answer.Ans1: The reign of Eric of Pomerania, the first monarch of the Kalmar Union, ended in 1442, approximately 45 years after the inception of the union in 1397. Eric of Pomerania faced numerous challenges during his reign, including power struggles with the nobility and conflicts within the union. His rule was marked by tensions and disagreements among the member kingdoms, leading to internal conflicts and rebellions. Eventually, he was deposed as king in Sweden and faced opposition in Denmark and Norway as well. These factors contributed to the end of Eric of Pomerania's reign and the subsequent instability of the Kalmar Union.
Answer.Res1: The reign of Eric of Pomerania in the Kalmar Union ended primarily due to political and power struggles within the union. Despite his efforts to maintain unity and centralize power, Eric faced opposition and resistance from the nobility and other influential figures in the member kingdoms. His attempts to assert his authority and consolidate power led to conflicts and tensions, particularly in Sweden.
